âœ… Goal: Learn how to cancel async tasks using CancellationToken.

7ï¸âƒ£ Handling Timeouts with Task.WhenAny()
Practice:
Create an async method FetchUserDataAsync() that:
Simulates fetching user data (takes 5 seconds).
Use Task.WhenAny() to:
Wait for either the user data or a timeout of 3 seconds.
If the timeout wins, throw a TimeoutException.
âœ… Goal: Learn how to handle timeouts efficiently in async programming.

8ï¸âƒ£ Using async IAsyncEnumerable<> (Async Streams)
Practice:
